gomodel:SYNGO_3785  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Syt11 inhibits endocytosis in neurons\"\n- \"we next determined whether the impaired DA transmission was also due to the inhibitory role of Syt11 in endocytosis in dopaminergic neurons...Furthermore, we used live imaging of the synaptophysin-pHluorin reporter, an assay for stimulated synaptic endocytosis/exocytosis (Fig. 4c), to monitor the function of Syt11 in endocytosis and vesicle recycling...we found a reduced paired-pulse ratio of DA release in ipsilateral striatal slices overexpressing Syt11\"\n\nFig.5: \"Syt11 inhibits vesicle pool replenishment in dopaminergic neurons\"\n- \"we found a reduced paired-pulse ratio of DA release in ipsilateral striatal slices overexpressing Syt11\". Experimental description: - \"The floxed Syt11-null mice were from The Jackson laboratory (strain B6.129-Syt11tm1Sud/J)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3785" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

